*.o
zig-out/
.zig-cache/

# Concurrency-spike build outputs: the spike READMEs' `zig build-exe`
# commands produce extensionless binaries (and e10's -femit-asm produces
# a .s listing). Ignore the exact documented names per directory rather
# than broad patterns, so any new artifact still shows up in git status
# and gets a deliberate decision (same rationale as the fork's S0.0
# exact-path entries).
concurrency-e1/bench
concurrency-e9/fiber_switch
concurrency-e9/wakeup
concurrency-e10/dispatch
*.s
